				<br /><hr>
				<span style="float: left;"><h3><strong>Deputy Store Manager</strong></h3></span>
				<span style="float: right;"><h3>September 2006 - October 2014</h3></span>
					
				<div style="margin-top: 85px;">
					<h4><em>Halfords, Cork ,Duties:</em></h4>
					<ul>
						<li>supporting the store manager in the day to day running of the store. Communicating targets and tasks at shift changes so as to provide a high level of customer service.</li>
                <li>Shop floor:  Responsible for day to day running of the shop floor in regards for merchandising, promotional changes ,pricing ,hygiene and service standards.</li>
                <li>Managing people:  Responsible for thirty staff members. I also deal with all H.R issues including development plans for staff through training and people management.</li>
				<li>Trading Account:  working with the store manager and department heads to keep controllable erosions in line in regard to payroll budgets, breakages, refunds, security and telephone.</li>
				<li>Back office:  Responsible for daily till and safe reconciliation's refund audits and all banking.</li>
                <li>Achievements:  Full responsibility for delivering the last 3 stock takes within the store, from planning to implementation and investigation.  I have filled the roll as area stock take invigilator for the last two years covering five stores.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<br /><hr>
			<span style="float: left;"><h3><strong>Store Manager</strong></h3></span>
				<span style="float: right;"><h3>July 2005 - September 2006</h3></span>
					
				<div style="margin-top: 85px;">
					<h4><em>Grandons Fine Food Fair, Glanmire</em></h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Sales, increased sales by 5% after a period of 6 months by correcting errors in margins and pricing with in the store as well as relaying the store to be more shopper friendly.</li>
				<li>Stock control/Variation control:  improved the levels of stock holding and wastage within the store with the introduction of stock cards and correct staff training in regards to stock management.</li>
				<li>Managing people:  Responsible for staff structure on a weekly basis. As well as all personnel management with regard to the store. I trained all staff in customer service. I provided training for key staff in stock and ordering as well as goods inwards and outwards. I identified 3 members of staff for key holding/supervisory duties who have gone on to careers in retail management.</li>
				<li>Hygiene:  Full working knowledge of H.A.C.C.P systems with regard to retail.</li>
				<li>E.P.O.S:  I was responsible for all E.P.O.S systems within the store. I have a full working knowledge of E.P.O.S systems.</li>
				<li>Banking:  I was responsible for all cashing up and banking procedures as well as all deposits at the bank on a bi weekly basis.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<br /><hr>
			<span style="float: left;"><h3><strong>Store Manager</strong></h3></span>
				<span style="float: right;"><h3>July 2005 - September 2006</h3></span>
				
					<div style="margin-top: 85px;">
					<h4><em>Fine Food Fair, Douglas, Cork</em></h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Duties:  To drive sales within the store across all departments.</li>
				<li>Sales:  To obtain the correct mix/range of stock across all departments from liquor to fresh to grocery.</li>
				<li>Stock control/Variation control:  improving and maintaining stock and ordering systems as well as security systems within the store.</li>
				<li>Managing people:  Responsible for staff structures on a weekly basis. Budgets where given and rosters had to be compiled within budget constraints. I have excellent communication and people management skills.</li>
				<li>Achievements:  Through successful management of our Deli, Hot food, Avanti pizza and in store bakery my Deli team and I won the cuisine de France food award for convenience stores up to 5,000 square feet.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
